A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a small red snail carrying a glowing data packet on its shell, slowly crawling across a massive tangled web of copper telephone wires and cables that stretch between two distant city skylines - one depicting Singapore's Marina Bay Sands on the left, the other showing generic American skyscrapers on the right. The background features a faded sepia-toned world map with dotted lines showing a convoluted, unnecessarily long path between the two cities. The snail leaves a trail of binary code (ones and zeros) behind it. Warm amber and burnt orange color palette with slightly yellowed paper texture, reminiscent of mid-century technical manuals and travel posters. No text or labels anywhere in the image.
